<LegalLayout frontmatter={{
  title: 'Privacy Policy — WhatsForLunch',
  description: 'How WhatsForLunch collects, uses, and protects your data.',
  lastUpdated: 'April 27, 2026',
}}>

<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>
  WhatsForLunch ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy.
  This policy explains what data we collect, why we collect it, and how you can
  control it.
</p>

<h2>1. What We Collect</h2>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Data</th><th>Why</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><strong>Email address</strong></td><td>Sign-in via magic link. Never used for marketing without your consent.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Food items &amp; expiry dates</strong></td><td>Core app functionality — stored locally on your device and optionally synced to your account.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Food photos</strong></td><td>Sent to our AI service (Amazon Rekognition) to identify the food item. Deleted from our servers immediately after classification unless you choose otherwise in Settings → Privacy.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Barcode scans</strong></td><td>Looked up against Open Food Facts (an open database). No personal data is sent.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Crash reports &amp; diagnostics</strong></td><td>Collected only if you opt in (Settings → Privacy → Share crash reports). Powered by Sentry. Contains device type, OS version, and a stack trace — no personal or food data.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Anonymous usage analytics</strong></td><td>Collected only if you opt in. Powered by PostHog. Helps us understand which features are used so we can improve the app.</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>2. What We Don't Do</h2>

<ul>
  <li>We <strong>never sell</strong> your data to third parties.</li>
  <li>We <strong>never use</strong> your food data for advertising.</li>
  <li>We <strong>never share</strong> your email with advertisers.</li>
  <li>We <strong>don't use</strong> tracking cookies on this website.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Local-First Storage</h2>

<p>
  All food data is stored <em>first on your device</em> using a local database.
  Cloud sync is used only to share data across your devices or with household
  members you explicitly invite. You can use the app entirely offline.
</p>

<h2>4. Household Sharing</h2>

<p>
  When you invite a person to your household, they can see the food items in that
  shared household. You control who is in your household and can remove members
  at any time in Settings → Households.
</p>

<h2>5. Data Retention</h2>

<p>
  We retain your account data for as long as your account is active.
  You can <strong>export all your data</strong> at any time from Settings → Privacy → Export my data,
  or <strong>permanently delete your account</strong> from Settings → Account → Delete Account.
  Deletion is irreversible and removes all data from our servers within 30 days.
</p>

<h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Privacy policy</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Amazon Web Services</td><td>Authentication, cloud sync, AI image analysis</td><td><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">aws.amazon.com/privacy</a></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Sentry (opt-in)</td><td>Crash reporting</td><td><a href="https://sentry.io/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sentry.io/privacy</a></td></tr>
    <tr><td>PostHog (opt-in)</td><td>Usage analytics</td><td><a href="https://posthog.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">posthog.com/privacy</a></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Open Food Facts</td><td>Barcode lookups</td><td><a href="https://world.openfoodfacts.org/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">openfoodfacts.org/privacy</a></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Expo / React Native</td><td>App runtime</td><td><a href="https://expo.dev/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expo.dev/privacy</a></td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>

<p>
  WhatsForLunch is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
  personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have done so
  inadvertently, please contact us and we will delete the data promptly.
</p>

<h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>

<p>
  We may update this policy as the app evolves. Material changes will be
  communicated via an in-app notification. Continued use of the app after changes
  take effect constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
</p>

<h2>9. Contact</h2>

<p>
  Questions or requests (including data deletion or access requests) can be sent to:
  <a href="mailto:privacy@whatsforlunch.app">privacy@whatsforlunch.app</a>
</p>

</LegalLayout>
